<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Roxboro </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Roxboro, along with the adjacent Rideau Park, is located inside the curve of the Elbow
                River. Both of these communities have evolved into a single entity. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The northern border is completely covered by the Elbow River, while the 4th Street SW runs
                along the western border of Roxboro. The Mission Road and the 33rd Avenue SW flank the southern border
                while to the east is the Macleod Trail. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The inner city residential community is in the southwest quadrant of Calgary, Alberta and
                was developed a few years after the neighboring Rideau Park.</p>

            <p class="par-lg">The location is the most desirable feature of this upscale, quiet neighborhood of Roxboro
                real estate. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">Fine dining, shopping, biking and hiking trails and parks are all within easy reach for
                residents. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes in Roxboro real estate can cost between $1 million to $4 million.</p>


